Amanda Khoza, News24Knife attack. (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A KwaZulu-Natal man risked his life fighting off a knife-wielding robber in his kitchen in the early hours of Tuesday morning, local police said.The Hillcrest resident, 44, woke up at 00:00 after hearing noises from his lounge, police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said.He went to investigate, found a man in his kitchen and shouted at him. The intruder grabbed a knife from the kitchen drawer and the two began scuffling.Meanwhile, a second suspect was banging on a window. A third man was waiting nearby.The home owner managed to push the intruder out of a window and all three men ran away empty-handed. The man sustained stab wounds to his left arm and forehead.Police are investigating a case of attempted house robbery.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.